        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20528",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=paulmenheere",
                        "name": "paulmenheere",
                        "displayName": "Paul Menheere",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It also affects version 1.5 and seems to be the problem with Microsoft SBS 2003 as mailtransport.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=paulmenheere",
                        "name": "paulmenheere",
                        "displayName": "Paul Menheere",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-31T09:18:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-31T09:18:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20833",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=toxygene",
                        "name": "toxygene",
                        "displayName": "Justin Hendrickson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This has been sitting out here for quite a while with no resolution and it's a very simple fix. If there's concern about breaking existing functionality, could we at least make th line length customizable, but defaults to 74, so those of us that need this change can actually use the mail library?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=toxygene",
                        "name": "toxygene",
                        "displayName": "Justin Hendrickson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-13T13:21:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-13T13:21:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21119",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please evaluate and categorize\/assign as necessary.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-18T15:48:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-18T15:48:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21706",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cocomp",
                        "name": "cocomp",
                        "displayName": "Jeremy Coates",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Just done some testing with one of our clients who has been seeing this corruption for every PDF attached.\n\nTheir environment Win2K3 server, Exchange 2K3 (v6.5.76381), XP & Vista Clients Outlook 2K3\n\nWidth 74 - PDF files arrive corrupted every time\nWidth 72 - PDF files arrive as expected\n\nImpact on other clients - non noticeable - e.g. SBS Exchange \/ Outlook 2K3, Thunderbird (multi-platform), Gmail, Hotmail, Yahoo! all work fine.\n\nI'd suggest we move to 72 width as the default (or at least have a configurable option as suggested).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cocomp",
                        "name": "cocomp",
                        "displayName": "Jeremy Coates",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-05-10T03:22:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-05-10T03:22:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21707",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cocomp",
                        "name": "cocomp",
                        "displayName": "Jeremy Coates",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Just to confirm, this is still an issue with 1.5.x ZF.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cocomp",
                        "name": "cocomp",
                        "displayName": "Jeremy Coates",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-05-10T03:24:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-05-10T03:24:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21710",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cocomp",
                        "name": "cocomp",
                        "displayName": "Jeremy Coates",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Further investigation seems to indicate switching to 72 is fine for PDFs but not e.g. Zip files.\n\nPerhaps there's a wider issue at work?!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cocomp",
                        "name": "cocomp",
                        "displayName": "Jeremy Coates",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-05-12T00:58:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-05-12T00:58:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/22273",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=numberxiii",
                        "name": "numberxiii",
                        "displayName": "Frederic Marchal",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Our customers have encountered this corruption for every file attached, not only PDF.\n\nTheir environment is : Exchange v6.5, Outlook 2K3\n\nI read the source of ezc, PHPmailer class and PEAR::Mail, and I found they all use a line length of 76.\n\nSo, I changed the constant LINELENGTH (line 41 of Mime.php) to 76, and it works well for every attachments.\nI do not tried zip files.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=numberxiii",
                        "name": "numberxiii",
                        "displayName": "Frederic Marchal",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-10T03:01:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-10T03:01:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23904",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=antych",
                        "name": "antych",
                        "displayName": "Karol Grecki",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There's a hotfix for it at http:\/\/support.microsoft.com\/default.aspx?scid=kb;EN-US;937625\nIt would still be nice to have some workaround for it as most corporate users won't install it untill next service pack is released.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=antych",
                        "name": "antych",
                        "displayName": "Karol Grecki",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-02T03:56:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-02T03:56:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25788",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed with r12343.\nChanged linelength to 72 to be compatible with other mailers.",
